					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=2457">North Freeport</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Knights Of Truth Acceptance</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Knights Of Truth Acceptance</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=3903"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:jrkasper@hotmail.com">Sir Thelion of the Knights of Truth</a> | 
		                        10/15/1999 10:20:06 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">I had submitted a broken question for this quest, but having recently completed it, I shall share, for many a Paladin seek to become a Knight of truth.<BR>
You may wish to become familiar with the sewers prior to this quest, for it instills serious faction with the militia and an escape rout is always handy.<BR>
First off, you must seek out Merko Quetalis, a guildmaster on the back lawn of the Hall Of Truth. Upon finding him, Hail him and converse with him.  If at one point you are told you are too high in experience, you must find a low level paladin to assist.<BR>
You should receive a note from Merko (or your new found friend who got you one) that needs to be takin to Altunic Jartin in the far west of the East Commonlands.<BR>
**The Note is tradeable &amp; Replaceable, just in case a lower lvl'd helper wonders**<BR>
Altunic will require you to Kill a Squire that has been disrupting business.  Squire Narls shows up moments later outside the hut.  He is near 11-12th lvl, so be ready and be careful.<BR>
Altunic Will have you run another errand and then give you the TOKEN OF GENEROSITY and a phrase to mention to Merko.  Go see Merko again and say the phrase, then you will be asked to retrieve another Item for him.  Find what he asks for and make sure the Token of Generosity is in a pack, as you hand him the item.  You will then receive a TOKEN OF COURAGE if you had the Generosity token stuffed in a pack.<BR>
Here's the tricky part.  When you give Merko the 2 tokens, a Guard named Willia appears in the sewer area there, so it may be good to have a few friends staking it.  Willia con's VERY easy to me, as I was lvl 16 upon doing this, and had to get the assistance of a wizard to root her.<BR>
Dispatch her and take what you Find to Merko.  You will receive a TESTAMENT OF TRUTH<BR>
<BR>
Welcome to the Knights of Truth.<BR>
<BR>
Sir Thelion of the Bristlebane server
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
