	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have recently finnished this quest. I did this quest twice. The 1st time I killed her. The second time I hailed her and talked to her. I was level 8 when I did this.<BR>
<BR>
The story is deeper than you think:<BR>
<BR>
Hail Guard Willia and she will talk to you about not killing her. She wants to leave the [Freeport Militia}.<BR>
<BR>
Ask her about the [Freeport Militia] and she will say something about being stuck [here] and asking for your forgiveness.<BR>
<BR>
Now ask her what are you stuck here...I know I know it is not proper English but it worked.<BR>
<BR>
She will talk to you about a problem she had with her aunt that left her red.  And that she came to ask [Merco to forgive]. Talk to her about [Merbo to forgive] and she will ask you to talk to Merco.<BR>
<BR>
When you talk to Merco ask him about Willia. &quot;Who is Willia?&quot; He then tells you that Willia is his neice who was sent by lunca to kill his wife (her aunt). Being the good little milita girl she did it. He will tell you kill Willia, that there is no excuse for militia all should die. <BR>
<BR>
This is where I am stuck.  I have tried to talk to Merco about her forgiveness. I have to give this DISCOLSURE:  I had another person keep will busy by having him hail here and talk to her to help figure it out. If anyone gets anymore answers I'll be happy to here<BR>
<BR>
BTW, if you ask her about the token of truth she will tell you that she had seen one like it in the pond.  <BR>
<BR>
I think that all the banter is to misdirect you so that she can get away.  But.....there might be more. ];&gt;
