	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To increase your faction with the Freeport Militia you can go to the Rogues Guild in E.Freeport. Go to to the docks and swim to the right, pass the shark then there's a cave entrance on the right. Thru here you'll find the Rogue guildmaster (female) guarded by a Gnome I think. In the next room there's two more rogues, one dwarf one human. Speak to the human who'll ask you to fetch him a dwarven ale. Bring the ale back and listen to the banter between the two rogues! The dwarf will give you a note to take to another rogue in Theatre of Tranquil.... Hand the note over and up goes your faction. He'll then give you another note to take back to the dwarf. You then get another faction increase and a very small reward. There are no negative faction hits. Don't know if a true paladin should do this, but I justified it to myself by reading the notes, to find out what they are up to!<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
